name: 골머체
contents: 곤머체고운 동산을 나타냄, 골머체로 와전되어 불림
engContents: this name was derived from Gonmeoche(beautiful hill)

name: 몰진-밧
contents: 말을 진상하기 위해 말을 모아 두었던 밭
engContents: this field used to be a place to collect horses before presenting them to the king
janContents: 馬を献上するために馬を集めていた畑

name: 개우지-코지
contents: 바닷가 쪽을 향해 쭉 뻗어 나가서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it got outstretched towards the sea
janContents: 海辺に向かってずっと伸びていることからつけられた名前

name: 성제-돌
engContents: this name suggests two rocks stand together like brothers
janContents: 石が二つ兄弟のように並んでいるところ

name: 테우리-통
contents: 소 먹이는 테우리가 망을 보던 곳
engContents: this place is where a taewoori(a herdboy) used to stand guard
janContents: 牛にえさを揚げている牧童が満月を見たところ
chiContents: 放牛的牧童守望的地方

name: 생이-돌
engContents: this means migratory birds have a rest on this stone
janContents: 渡り鳥が座って遊んでいた石

name: 누릉낭-동산
engContents: this means a hill of elm trees

name: 독-통
engContents: this name suggests a look of a hen sitting on eggs

name: 섬들이-왓
engContents: this name suggests this is a palce where islands are not visible
janContents: 島が見えない地域のことをいう

name: 한지내-콤
contents: 내가 넓은 모양. 한지는 넓다 이고 콤은 일정지역을 나타냄
engContents: this name consists of Hanji(wide) and Kom(a certain place)
janContents: 中が広い様子、ハンジ は広いという意味でコム は一定の地域を表す

name: 맹-살
contents: 비가 많이 와서 범람하면 물로 채워지는 곳
engContents: this place used to be filled with water when flooding
janContents: 雨がたくさん降って氾濫した水であふれているところ

name: 쇠소-깍
contents: 하효마을의 본래 명칭은 쇠둔이다. 효돈천하구에 있는 소라 하여 쇠소라불려지고 있으며, 쇠소의 마지막이라하여 붙여진 이름 깍은 맨마지막을 나타냄
engContents: the original name of Hahyo village is Soedun. this word consists of Soeso meaning a swamp at the end of Hyodoncheon(Hyodon stream) and Kkak meaning the last
janContents: 下孝村の本来の名称はセドゥン である。孝敦川 の河口にあるサザエをセソ と呼ばれており、その最後であることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 下孝村原名“牛屯”。因位于“下孝川”河口的牛而称作“孝牛”。因为是最后一头孝牛而得名。

name: 소금-막
contents: 막은 막사를 의미, 소금을 구웠던 곳
engContents: this place used to be a spot for burning salt
janContents: マク はバラックを意味、塩をあぶっていたところ

name: 소나물-곳
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the depth of the place is quite long
janContents: 水が深いところを意味する

name: 재-통
contents: 모몰짚을 태워 재를 만들었던 곳, 모몰은 메밀
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it used to be a place to get ash(Jae) from burning straws
janContents: ソバのわらを燃やして灰をつくっていたところモムル はソバの意

name: 도-틀-왓
engContents: this name suggests that it is a field open to the road

name: 돌박남-밧
engContents: this name suggests the place used to be a field full of camellias(Dongbaeknamu)

name: 닥-돌래
contents: 닥은 닥나무, 돌레는 둥그렇게 생긴 작은 밭이다. 닥나무를 재배했던 곳
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it used to be the place to cultivate Dak trees(paper mulberry)
janContents: タク はコウゾ、トルレ は円くて小さな畑の意で、コウゾを栽培していたところ

name: 고막-곶
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was used to be a forest
janContents: 前は森であったことからつけられた名前

name: 믠-돌
contents: 믠은 믠짝으로 아무것도 없음을 말함. 즉 주위에 아무것도 없이 돌만 있는 곳
engContents: this name was derived from the word, Myeun meaning there is nothing but stones
janContents: 周りに何もなく石だけあるところ

name: 써금-바령
contents: 소, 말 등을 밤에 풀어두었던 곳
engContents: this place used to be a spot for releasing cows and horses at night
janContents: 牛・馬などを夜放し飼いにしておいたところ

name: 큰-가름
contents: 마을 안에 또하나의 큰마을을 이룬 것
engContents: it means a large village in another village
janContents: 村の中にもう一つ大きい村ができること
chiContents: 村庄里面又形成了一个大村庄

name: 구덕찬-돌
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of stone with holes
janContents: 石の形が具德 の姿をしている

name: 애기업게-돌
engContents: this name came from the stone having a look of one carrying a baby on the back
janContents: 石の形が子供をおぶっている姿をしている

name: 왜-통
engContents: it used to be a place to manufacture tiles
janContents: 瓦をつくっていたところ

name: 노용-동산
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a roe
janContents: ノロの形のような地形

name: 말축-밧
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a horse leg

name: 천아오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is an oak tree
janContents: クヌギの木があることに由来

name: 정물오름
engContents: this name was derived from a fountain name,  Jeongmul,
janContents: ジョンムル という泉があることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 因有称作“井水”的泉而得名

name: 새미소오름
contents: 깊은 샘이 있는 오름이라 붙여진 이름
engContents: it means a hill with a deep well
janContents: 深い泉がある山であることからつけられた名前

name: 느지리오름
engContents: this name was derived from Neujiri, the former name of Sangmyeongri
janContents: 上明里の昔の名前ヌジリ に由来

name: 갯거리오름
contents: 두 마리의 개가 꼬리를 끌고 누운 형상에서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of two dogs lying down with their tails outstreched
janContents: 頭が二つのイヌがしっぽを引いて寝ている形に由来

name: 마오름
contents: 산이 말 형체를 하고 있어 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a horse
janContents: 山が馬の形をしていることに由来

name: 송아오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a calf
janContents: 子牛の形をしていることに由来

name: 노꼬물오름
contents: 노꼬물 전설에서 유래한 샘이 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the well known in the Nokomul legend
janContents: ノコムル伝説に由来した泉があることからつけられた名前

name: 가마오름
janContents: 神秘的な山であるという意味に由来

name: 염통오름
contents: 사람 가슴 안의 심장 형국이라 하여 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a human heart
janContents: 人の心臓の形であることに由来

name: 가세오름
contents: 산봉오리가 두 갈래로 갈라진것이 가위(가세)와 같아 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of the mountain top divided into two like scissors
janContents: 山の峰が二つに分かれているのがハサミのようであることに由来
chiContents: 分成两部分的山峰形同剪刀而得名

name: 벵곳오름
engContents: this name was allegedly derived from the fact there were byeongkotpul(ground ivy)
janContents: コウライヤブウツギがあることに由来した名前と推測

name: 번널오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a board

name: 백약이오름
engContents: this suggests there are one hundred kinds of herbs growing
janContents: 百種類の薬草が生えていることに由来

name: 산굼부리
engContents: this word consists of a hole(Gum) and a mountaintop(Buri)
janContents: 穴、山の頂上を意味する

name: 부대오름
contents: 화전, 개간지의 뜻인 부대기의 줄인말인듯 하나 확실치 않음
engContents: this name was possibly derived from the word, Budaegi meaning the ground burned off for cultivation or developed land
janContents: 火田、開拓地の意味であるブデキ の略語であるといわれるが確かではない

name: 바농오름
engContents: this name came from the forest full of thornbush
janContents: とげのある木がもつれている森があることに由来

name: 돔베오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the hill looks as even as a chopping board
janContents: まな板のように平たいことに由来
chiContents: 形同砧板般平坦而得名

name: 구그네오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance of a Gugeune(rake)
janContents: えぶり(農具の一種)に似ていることに由来

name: 궤펭이오름
engContents: this name suggests that there is a rock cave(Goe)
janContents: 岩の洞窟が掘られているという意味に由来

name: 까끄레기
contents: 마소를 방목한다는 말인 고끄레 간다는데서 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the words, Goggre ganda meaning farming cows and horses
janContents: 笑顔を繰り返すという韓国語であるコクレカンダ に由来

name: 흙붉은오름
contents: 붉은 흙의 산등이 멀리서 보일만큼 드러나 있어서 연유
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the ridge covered with red earth is seen from a distance
janContents: 赤土の尾根が遠くから見えるほど現れていることに由来

name: 족은드레오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the hill is standing in the small field(Jokeundeure)
janContents: 小さい野原にあることに由来

name: 큰드레오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the hill is standing in the large field(Keudeure)

name: 베리오름
contents: 오름의 바닷가쪽에 벼랑(베리)이 있다 하여 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a cliff(Byeorang) to the direction of the sea from this hill
janContents: 山の海側に断崖があることに由来した名前

name: 베두리오름
contents: 오름머리 남쪽에 별무리처럼 바위가 모여있다 하여 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the fact many rocks gather south of the top like a group of stars
janContents: 山頂の南に星屑のように岩が集まっていることに由来
chiContents: 山头南部的岩石星罗棋布而得名

name: 불칸디오름
engContents: this name means a burnt hill(Bulkandi)
janContents: 火がついて焼けたところという意味がある

name: 쌀손장오리
engContents: this name was derived from the legend three spirits shot arrows from this hill
janContents: 三神人が矢を射った火山であることに由来

name: 태역장오리
engContents: this name suggests there used to be a large lawn

name: 도들오름
engContents: it means the way it rises looks beautiful
janContents: 突き出ている姿が美しいことに由来

name: 노리오름
engContents: this name suggests there used to be lots of roes
janContents: ノロが多かったところに由来

name: 노리손이
contents: 노리는 노루를, 손은 쏘다의 옛말로 노루가 많아 노루사냥으로 이름났던 데서 연유
engContents: this name is combination of a word, Nori(roe) and another word, Soni(shoot), which means it is popular for roe hunting
janContents: ノロが多くノロの狩の場所であったことに由来

name: 광이오름
engContents: this name was derived from the features of a cat
janContents: 地形がクワのようであることに由来

name: 남짓은오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks overgrown with trees
janContents: 木が茂っていることに由来

name: 골머리오름
engContents: this name suggests this is the first top of ninty nine hill tops
janContents: 99の洞窟の一番初めに当たることに由来
chiContents: 九十九谷的第一谷而得名

name: 걸시오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a latch
janContents: 地形がㄱの形の掛け金のようであることに由来

name: 거친오름
contents: 몸집이 크고 산세가 험한데다 숲이 어수선히 우거져 거칠게 보여 연유함
engContents: this name suggests this big mountain has steep and bumpy features and the forest is overgrown with trees
janContents: 山が大きくて険しく森がうっそうと茂っており荒く見えることに由来

name: 솔오름
contents: 쌀을 쌓아올린 형태, 살(피부)처럼 매끈하다 하여 유래했다는 등의 의견이 있음
engContents: this name is interpreted in many ways; the looks of a stack of rice or as smooth as human skin and etc.
janContents: 米を積みあげた形、肌のようにすべすべしていることに由来しているなどの意見がある
chiContents: 源于堆起的大米、像皮肤一样滑嫩等

name: 시오름
engContents: this name was derived from Suoreum(Male-oreum)
janContents: 雄の山が誤って伝えられたもの

name: 베린내오름
contents: 벼랑(베리)을 이루는 천제연 근처에 있어 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is located near to Cheonjeyeon forming a cliff(Byoerang)
janContents: 断崖を成す天帝淵の近くにあることに由来
chiContents: 位于形成绝壁的天帝渊附近而得名

name: 방애오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of Banga(mill)
janContents: うすの形に似ていることに由来

name: 더데오름
contents: 더더(加加)에서 온 것으로 산이 중첩돼 있음을 뜻함
engContents: this name suggests the looks of mountain upon mountain
janContents: ドド から来た言葉で山が幾重にも重なっていることを意味

name: 넉시오름
contents: 넋 나간 소가 누워있는 형국에서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of an absent-minded cow lying down
chiContents: 形同躺着的失魂的牛而得名

name: 걸세오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a latch
janContents: ㄱの形の掛け金の形の山であることに由来

name: 이승이오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a wildcat
janContents: 山猫のような形であることに由来

name: 체오름
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of a winnow(che)
janContents: 箕の形をしていることに由来

name: 윤드리오름
contents: 넓은 들에 누워있는 오름이라 하나 어원이 확실치 않음
engContents: this name was allegedly derived from an orem(hill) lying down on a large field, which hasnt been ascertained
janContents: 広い野原に寝そべっている寄生火山だといわれるが語源ははっきりしない

name: 식은이오름
contents: 산맥이 벌써 식었다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name means the mountains have got cold
janContents: 山脈がすでに消え去ったことからつけられた名前

name: 밭돌오름
contents: 돌이 많은 오름이나 안돌오름과 구별하기 위해 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was given to this stony hill in order to distinguish from Andoloreum
janContents: 石が多い火山でアンドルオルム と区別するためにつけられた名前

name: 안돌오름
contents: 돌이 많은 오름이나 밭돌오름과 구별하기 위해 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was given to this stony hill in order to distinguish from Baldoloreum
janContents: 石が多い火山でバンドルオルム と区別するためにつけられた名前

name: 아진오름
contents: 두 다리를 벌리고 앉아있는 모양에서 연유함
engContents: this name was derived from the looks one is sitting down with two legs outstretched
janContents: 日本の足を広げて座っている形に由来

name: 아부오름
engContents: this used to be once called Aporeum  but later changed into Abuoreum
janContents: 前の火山(アプ　オルム)からアブオルムに変形

name: 손지오름
contents: 작지만 한라산과 비슷하게 생겨 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it takes after Mountain Halla as if a grandson(Sonja) of it
janContents: 小さいが漢拏山と似ていることからつけられた名前

name: 비치미
contents: 꿩이 나는 형국이라 하여 붙여졌다 하나 확실치 않음
engContents: this name was allegedly derived from the appearance like a flying pheasant
janContents: キジが出る形であることからつけられたといわれているがはっきりしていない

name: 북오름
engContents: this name was derived from the look of a drum
janContents: 太鼓の形に似ていることからつけられた名前

name: 민오름
engContents: this name was derived from the smooth appearance
janContents: 形がすらっとしていることからつけられた名前

name: 돝오름
janContents: 山の形が豚のようであることからつけられた名前

name: 당오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be a shrine
janContents: 祠があったことからつけられた名前

name: 다랑쉬
contents: 산봉우리 분화구가 달처럼 둥글게 보인다 하여 붙여짐
engContents: this name was derived from the looks of the crater like the moon
janContents: 山頂の噴火口が月のように円く見えることからつけられた
chiContents: 山峰的喷火口形同圆月而得名

name: 거친오름
contents: 크고 거칠어보인다, 거쳐가는 오름이다, 거린오름의 와전이다 등의 유래가 있음
engContents: it has many interpretations such as big and rough, a transit hill, a name derived from Georin hill and etc.
janContents: 大きく荒れて見える、荒れている寄生火山だ、

name: 거슨새미오름
contents: 물이 한라산쪽으로 흘러나온다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water flows towards Mountain Halla
janContents: 水が漢拏山の方へ流れることからつけられた名前

name: 거미오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance its ridges are spreading in all directions like a spider web
janContents: 四方へ尾根を伸ばした姿がクモの巣に似ていることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 山脊向四面八方延伸，形同蜘蛛而得名

name: 쇠머리오름
contents: 우도의 형상이 소의 형상이고 그 머리부위에 해당하여 유래함
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it looks like a head of cow
janContents: 牛刀の形が牛の形でその頭の部分に該当することに由来

name: 쳇망오름
janContents: ふるいの枠の形であることに由来

name: 초낭오름
janContents: クヌギの木があることに由来

name: 이달오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there are two mountains(Dal)
janContents: 二つの山があることに由来

name: 사제비오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact sparrow hawks are living here
janContents: ハイタカが生息していることに由来

name: 빈네오름
contents: 봉우리 쪽에 쪽진 머리에 비녀를 꽂은 모습을 한 바위가 있어 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a rock looking like a lady with a hair pin(Binyeo) on the top
janContents: 峰の方に髪を束ねてかんざしをさしている形の岩があることに由来

name: 물메오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a pond on the top
janContents: 峰の上に池があることに由来

name: 노로오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there are lots of roes(Noro)
janContents: ノロがたくさん生息していることに由来

name: 폭낭오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be a big hackberry(Poknang)
janContents: 大きいエノキがあることに由来

name: 하늬복이오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is locatd where the north wind(Hanibaram) frequently blows
janContents: 北風がよく吹くところにあることに由来

name: 마복이오름
contents: 남풍(마파람)이 많이 부는 곳에 있어 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it is locatd where the south wind(Maparam) frequently blows
janContents: 南風がよく吹くところにあることに由来

name: 바굼지오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance having a look of bat
janContents: コウモリの形であったことに由来

name: 도너리오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it has a large entrance
janContents: 入り口がかなり広々としていることに由来

name: 넙게오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance having a look of a large crab
janContents: 平らで大きいカニの形であることに由来

name: 골른오름
contents: 쌍둥이(골오기)에서 유래하여 두오름이 나란히 있다 하여 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the word Gologi(twins), whose twin hills are standing side by side.

name: 굴메오름
engContents: it means this mountain happened to generate as an additional outcome
janContents: おまけとして生じた山という意味に由来

name: 거린오름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance that the hill is divided into two
janContents: 分かれた寄生火山という意味に由来

name: 족은물뫼
engContents: people call this small hill this way to distinguish from Keunmulmoe(big hill)
janContents: 大きいムルメ と区別するために呼ばれるようになった

name: 큰물뫼
contents: 원래 물뫼(물미)라 했던것이 동쪽의 족은물뫼와 구별하여 큰쿨뫼라 하게 됨
engContents: this used to be called Mulmoe once but later called Keunmulmoe as distinguishment fromJokeunmulmoe in the east
janContents: もともとムルメ と言っていたのを東方の小さいムルメと区別するためにクンクルメ となった

name: 족은왕뫼
contents: 왕뫼 가까이에 있는 작은 오름이라는데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this small hill is standing near to Wangmoe
janContents: 王の墓の近くにある小さな寄生火山であることに由来した名前
chiContents: 王山附近的小山而得名

name: 왕뫼
engContents: this hill name was derived from its look of prince
janContents: 皇太子のような形であり山脈がこの寄生火山から延びているといわれる

name: 유건에오름
contents: 유생이 쓰는 유건의 모양처럼 생겼다 하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its look of Korean traditional student hat
janContents: 儒生が使う冠の形のようであることに由来した名前
chiContents: 形同儒生的儒巾而得名

name: 본지오름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be lots of the oriental bittersweets
janContents: ツルウメモドキが多いことに由来した名前

name: 바우오름
contents: 바위가 많이 드러난 봉우리에서 바위가 바우로 변형되 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its top with lots of rocks
janContents: 岩がたくさん現れている峰で岩の意であるバウィ がバウ に変化したことに由来した名前

name: 젯그린동산
contents: 어미의 젖을 그리는 어린 개의 형국에서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its look of a puppy missing its mother dogs milk
janContents: 母親の乳を恋しがる子犬の形に由来した名前

name: 뒤굽은이
contents: 남동쪽을 산머리로 하여 북쪽으로 등성마루가 구부러져 있다 하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it has its head in the south east and the ridge in the north
janContents: 南東を山頂として北の方に山の背が曲がっていることに由来した名前

name: 통오름
contents: 물통, 밥통 등의 통처럼 생겼다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name reflects it looks like a container such as a water bottle or a rice bowl
janContents: 水筒・おひつなど筒の形に似ていることからつけられた名前

name: 돌미
contents: 동쪽 산머리에 큰 바위무더기가 박힌 돌산이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this stony mountain has a huge file of rocks in the east head
janContents: 東の山頂に大きい岩が突き刺さっている岩山であることからつけられた名前

name: 낭끼오름
contents: 나무들이 서 있는 변두리라는 뜻에서 유래
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was a countryside having trees around
janContents: 木が立っている町外れだという意味に由来

name: 통바금물
contents: 냇물이 고이는 곳이 우물(통)처럼 생겨서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the place to form a puddle looks like a well
janContents: 海の水がたまっているところが井戸のようであることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 河水积聚的地方形同深井（桶）而得名

name: 행기소물
contents: 샘의 모양이 밥사발 같고 물이 맑고 항상 고여있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it has a look of rice bowl and constantly running clear water
janContents: 泉の形がどんぶりの様で水がきれいでいつもたまっていることからつけられた名前

name: 등창물
contents: 맑은 샘이 아무리 가물어도 바닥을 드러내지 않는다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact this cear water never runs dry
janContents: きれいな泉がどんなに日照りが続いても底が現れないことからつけられた名前

name: 당두둑물
contents: 설문대할망당이 있는 두둑이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this ridge name was named after Seolmunhalmangdang
janContents: ソルムンデおばあさんの祠 があるあぜであることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 建有雪慢台女神堂的堤坝而得名

name: 겐놉샘물
contents: 물통처럼 둥그렇게 생기고 갯이끼가 껴있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: 물통처럼 둥그렇게 생기고 갯이끼가 껴있어 붙여진 이름
janContents: 形如水桶，还长有青苔而得名	水筒のように丸い形で海ゴケがくっついていることからつけられた名前

name: 새기미산물
contents: 차고 맑은 샘이 연중 마르지 않고 흐른다 해 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact cold and clear water springs up all the year round
janContents: 冷たくてきれいな泉が年中枯れることなく湧いている事からつけられた名前
chiContents: 清凉的泉水一年四季流淌而得名

name: 고씨땅물
contents: 고씨성을 가진 사람 땅 부근에 샘이 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it was located near Mr.Gos property
janContents: 高という姓の人の土地の近くに泉があることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 位于高氏的土地附近而得名

name: 고능개물
contents: 바닷가 소하천의 앞 바다가 가느다랗다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: the name was derived from the fact the front sea looks thin
janContents: 海辺の小さな河川前の海が細くなっていることからつけられた名前

name: 산열이통물
contents: 더위를 식히고 땀띠를 없애기 위해 이용하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water was used to release the heat and cure the heat rashes
janContents: 暑さをやわらげあせもを無くすために利用したことからつけられた名前
chiContents: 用于消暑、祛汗疹而得名

name: 노단새미
contents: 노단은 오른쪽을 일컫는 제주지역어로,  한라산을 향해 거슬러 흐르지 않는데서 유래한 이름
engContents: Nodan means a right direction in Jeju dialect and this name was derived from the fact it does not flow  in the direction of Halla Mountain
janContents: 右側をさす済州地域の言葉で漢拏山に向かって流れないということに由来する名前

name: 거슨새미
contents: 한라산쪽으로 거슬러 흐르는 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it flows upward in the direction of Halla Mountain
janContents: 漢拏山の方へ流れる泉であることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 泉水向汉拿山方向逆流而得名

name: 옥빰물
contents: 올빼미가 밤마다 운다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact owls sing every night
janContents: フクロウが毎夜鳴くことからつけられた名前

name: 괴물
contents: 궤에서 나오는 물이라 하여 궤물, 괴물이라 함
engContents: this name was derived from Goe
janContents: 天然の洞窟から湧く水であることからつけられた名前

name: 통물
engContents: this name was derived from the village called Tongcheonri

name: 양재소물
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there used to be Yangjaeso

name: 이당장물
contents: 당장 직함을 가진 이씨가 팠다 하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the well was dug by Mr.Lee having a title of Dangjang
janContents: 肩書きを持った李氏が掘ったといわれることに由来する名前

name: 감수물
engContents: this name was derived from its sweetness
janContents: 水が甘いことから甘水という

name: 양가수
contents: 양씨가 판 샘물이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the fountain was dug by Mr. Yang
janContents: ヤン氏が掘り当てた泉であることからつけられた名前

name: 넘나물
contents: 비가 오면 물이 넘친다 하여 지어진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water got overflown when it rained
janContents: 雨が降ると水があふれることからつけられた名前

name: 알정물
engContents: this name means a well on the downside
janContents: 下にある水という意味

name: 웃정물
contents: 우마가 들어가지 못하게 정을 놓은데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact they posted a bar to keep cows and horses away
janContents: 牛馬が入らないように精霊ををおいたことに由来する名前

name: 곤물
contents: 고은물로 부르다가 곤물이 되었다는 설과 곶물이 곤물이 되었다는 설이 있다
engContents: according to two interpretations, one is the name came from Goeunmul and the other is it came from Gotmul
janContents: コウンムル からコンムル になったという説とゴッムル がコンムル になったという説がある

name: 산통물
contents: 넘치는법 없이 늘 그만큼 채워져 있어 살아있는 물이라 하여 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the water is always filled up as same as if it is alive
janContents: あふれることなく適度にたまっていて生きている水であることに由来する名前
chiContents: 从不溢出，始终保持一定水量的活水而得名

name: 가르메물
contents: 사람 머리꼭대기 정수리처럼 생겼다 하여 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the appearance of the top looking like a human head
janContents: 人の頭のてっぺんのようであることに由来する名前

name: 부개높물
contents: 물고기들이 펄쩍펄쩍 뛰는게 보인다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it can have a view of fish jumping out of the water
janContents: 魚がピョンピョンはねるのが見えることからつけられた名前

name: 몰성괴물
contents: 수산평의 말과 소를 이 포구에서 선적하여 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact horses and cows from Susanpyeong used to be shipped at this port
janContents: 水山坪の馬と牛をこの浦口から船積みしたことに由来する名前

name: 며느리다리물
contents: 한 집 며느리가 밤에 당을 찾아가다 빠져 죽은 후로 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the legend a housewife happened to be drown in this water while going to the shrine at night
janContents: ある嫁が夜にお堂を探している途中に落ちて死んでしまったことに由来する名前
chiContents: 一家的媳妇夜里到祠堂途中失足淹死而得名

name: 색통물
contents: 소들이 즐겨 물을 먹었던 곳에서 연유한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact cows used to drink this water
janContents: 牛が好んで水を飲んだところに由来する名前
chiContents: 成群的牛喜欢到此地喝水而得名

name: 앞펄
contents: 앞쪽에 있는 펄 이름을 따서 붙여진 이름
engContents: this was named after the tideland ahead
janContents: 前のほうにある干潟の名前を取ってつけた名前

name: 주군디물
contents: 군대가 주둔할 당시 그들이 이용한 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact soldiers used to drink this water while thier stationing
janContents: 軍隊が駐屯時に利用した泉であることからつけられた名前

name: 수전
contents: 조선 초기에 수전소가 있던곳이라 하여 유래된 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its origin as the navy camp in Chosun Kingdom
janContents: 朝鮮時代初期に水戦所があったところであることに由来した名前
chiContents: 朝鲜初期曾建有水电站而得名

name: 당두포
contents: 오조리 당의 머리쪽에 있는 포구라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the port was located at the head of Ojoridang(shrine)
janContents: 吾照里の祠の頭のほうにある浦口であることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 位于吾照里祠堂前面的浦口而得名

name: 큰개물
contents: 마을의 중심이 되는 큰 포구가 있는 곳에 있어 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its location in the large port as the center of the village
janContents: 村の中心となる大きい
chiContents: 位于村庄中心的大浦口而得名

name: 테우리동산물
contents: 근처의 동산에서 백중제를 지낸데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact they performed a religious service for a good harvest
janContents: 近くの山で百中祭を行うことに由来する名前
chiContents: 在附近山上举行百中祭而得名

name: 배탕개물
contents: 근처에 배탕개란 지명이 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the place name, Baetanggae in the neighborhood
janContents: 近くにベタンゲ という地名があることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 附近有“排唐浦”地名而得名

name: 진모살물
contents: 포구 근처에 모래밭이 길게 펼쳐져 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact there is a long sand bed near the port
janContents: 浦口の近くに砂浜が長く広がっていることからつけられた名前

name: 코지산물
contents: 근처에 사람 코의 형상의 바위가 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the rock having a look of human nose nearby
janContents: 近くに人の鼻の形をした岩があることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 附近有形同人鼻的岩石而得名

name: 앞개물
contents: 마을 앞에 자리잡았다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the location in front of the village
janContents: 村の前に位置していることからつけられた名前

name: 만물
contents: 근처 바닷가 일대가 조그마한 만을 형성하고 있어 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the seashore forms a small gulf
janContents: 近くの海辺一帯が小さな湾を形成していることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 附近海边一带形成了小小村庄而得名

name: 대머들물
contents: 지형지세가 개의 형국이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name derived from the natural features looking like  a dog
janContents: 地形地勢が犬の形であることからつけられた名前

name: 호근여물
contents: 범의 아가리 형태의 여 근처에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its location near the rocks having a look of the mouth of tiger
janContents: 虎の口の形の暗礁の近くにあることからつけられた名前
chiContents: 位于形同虎口的礁石附近而得名

name: 농개물
contents: 고기를 잡으려 투망하던 목이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact it used to be the place to throw a cast net
janContents: 魚を捕まえるために網を投げたところであることからつけられた名前

name: 분드르물
contents: 마을과 멀리 분리하여 떨어진 들판이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from the fact the field is separated way long from the village
janContents: 村と遠く離れている野原であることからつけられた名前

name: 괸물
engContents: it originally means a still water
janContents: たまっている水という意味に由来した名前

name: 큰물
contents: 수량이 풍부하고 큰 샘이라는데서 유래한 이름
engContents: this is a large fountain having an abundant amount of water
janContents: 水量が豊富で大きい泉であることに由来した名前
chiContents: 水量丰富且大的泉而得名

name: 주어미수개미동굴
contents: 다양한 어족이 모여드는 바닷가에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this is located in front of a sea having different species of fish
janContents: さまざまな魚類が集まる海辺にあることからつけられた名前

name: 주어물
contents: 다양한 어족이 모여드는 바닷가에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this is located in front of a sea having different species of fish
janContents: さまざまな魚類が集まる海辺にあることからつけられた名前

name: 모살-꼽지
engContents: this name suggests that it is a sandy corner
janContents: 砂が多い奥まったところ

name: 엉앞물
contents: 바위그늘 앞 바닷가에 있다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain is located in the shade of rocks at the seashore.
janContents: 岩陰の前の海辺にあることからつけられた名前

name: 고른-참
contents: 대정현과 정의현의 경계선, 참은 5리를 나타내는 거리의 단위로서 말을 바꾸어 타던 장소
engContents: this place is a border between Daejeonghyeon and Jeongeuihyeon, where they used to change horses to ride. Cham means 5 ris as a measuring unit of distance
janContents: 大靜縣と旌義縣の境界線、チャム は5里をあらわす距離の単位で馬を乗り換える場所

name: 동물
contents: 새모슬촌락의 동쪽에 있는 샘이라 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this fountain is located in the east of Saemoseul village
janContents: セモスル 村落の東側にある泉であることからつけられた名前

name: 조개물
contents: 조개하나 크기만큼 작다 하여 붙여진 이름
engContents: this name was derived from its small size as a shell
janContents: 貝一つほどのしかなく小さいことからつけられた名前

name: 조선물
